cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.DS 

This paper is about query auto-completion, which is a common feature of search systems. The paper discusses the challenge of designing an optimal engine that considers and uses all available information, and proposes an alternative strategy of aggregating several engines to enhance the diversity of recommendations. This topic is closely related to information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
